  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - ENCHANTER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>TO BLAST, OR NOT TO BLAST-</font> - <small>Aenr D'Zav, Povar</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>This really isn't the question,the 
answer is simple. DON'T BLAST! 
*grin*
<P>
I get very frustrated when I group 
with other enchanters, and see them 
casting 2, sometimes 3 DD spells in 
a fight.  The damage to mana ratio 
of enchanter DDs is among the worst 
of any casting class.  Don't make 
the mistake of thinking you're a 
wizard.
<P>
The true power of the enchanter is 
in crowd control, especially after 
lvl 20.  You're an insurance policy 
for when the group pulls too much.  
Yes, when the group pulls one, you 
can be helpful by de-buffing, but 
don't use all your mana unless it's 
so big a MOB that you're group needs it.
<P>
4 spells I always have memorized 
when fighting in places such as 
Cazic Thule, where overpulling 
happens constantly, are Enthrall, 
mesmerization, color shift, and 
color flux.  The first thing you 
need to do is explain to your group 
to ALWAYS /assist whoever is 
pulling, so that you can mez the 
rest, otherwise your group will just keep waking the rest up.
<P>
Your entire job now is to mesmerize 
any extra MOBs that come, and keep 
them mesmerized until the group is 
ready for them.  If the MOBs are 
only yellow or less, and close 
together, you can alternate color 
spells. color flux first and as soon as you can, color shift.  then the 
MOBs will un-stun right about the 
same time color flux is ready, so do it again. you can keep whole groups 
of MOBs stunned with this combo, the whole fight.  Be wared- it can 
sometimes get messy if they resist, 
so avoid doing this when there are 
several red MOBs.  In this situation you are best off individually 
tashani'ing and enthralling each 
extra MOB.
<P>
In times where things are going slow and you have extra mana, go ahead 
and slap quickness on people. The 
only time you should ever actually 
blast something, is if it's running 
away, and your group is 
concentrating on something else.  If you can prevent the train it would 
start if it got away, blast your 
heart out. If your group is with you trying to stop it though, just color flux/shift it.
<P>
That's the end of my advice.  Keep 
in mind your job is crowd control, 
and your groups will love you.  I 
have been consistently praised in my groups in Cazic Thule, groups of 
mostly 26-30, where I am only 23. 
Leave the blasting to the wizards, 
and go take control of the fight.
<P>
-Aenr D'Zav</td></tr>
